FBIS4-15911 "drsov071_e_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-071 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Kiev Places Black Sea Fleet at Odessa Under Army Kiev Places Black Sea Fleet at Odessa Under Army AU1204151094 Paris AFP in English 1459 GMT 12 Apr 94 AU1204151094 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Kiev, 12 April (AFP) -- Ukraine has placed the Black Sea Fleet based at Odessa under the authority of the Ukrainian Army, Deputy Defence Minister Ivan Bijan was quoted by the INTERFAX-UKRAINE news agency as saying on Tuesday [12 April]. Talks to end a row between Russia and Ukraine over the fate of the fleet began earlier Tuesday in Kiev between a Russian delegation headed by Admiral Felix Gromiv and Ukrainian Armed Forces chief of staff General Anatoly Lopata.
